TITLE: How Elon Musk could impact Twitter's battles over speech abroad
SUMMARY: Since Elon Musk announced he was buying Twitter last month, the billionaire has sent out tweet after tweet outlining his plans for the platform, touching on everything from new features to security updates to monetization. But Musk's overarching reason for committing billions of dollars to buy Twitter is to ensure the platform bolsters free speech.

TITLE: Search histories, location data, text messages: How personal data could be used to enforce anti-abortion laws
SUMMARY: A wave of new legislation taking aim at abortion rights across the country is raising concerns about the potential use of personal data to punish people who seek information about or access to abortion services online.

TITLE: Judge dismisses Trump lawsuit against Twitter over ban
SUMMARY: A federal judge in San Francisco has dismissed former President Donald Trump's lawsuit against Twitter that sought to reinstate his banned account on the platform, according to a court filing.

TITLE: Musk's $44 billion Twitter buyout challenged in shareholder lawsuit
SUMMARY: Elon Musk and Twitter were sued on Friday by a Florida pension fund seeking to stop Musk from quickly completing his planned $44 billion takeover of the social media company.

TITLE: Nvidia misled investors about impact of crypto mining on its business, SEC alleges
SUMMARY: For years, video gamers have blamed shortages of PC graphics cards on cryptocurrency enthusiasts, who have snapped up growing numbers of the devices to generate digital coins. The pandemic, along with the Trump administration's tariffs on Chinese imports, have only made the situation worse, leading to skyrocketing retail and aftermarket prices.

TITLE: Kraft Heinz wants to solve its supply chain problems — in the metaverse
SUMMARY: Kraft Heinz is using the metaverse to help get Lunchables, Velveeta and ketchup onto shelves faster.

TITLE: SpaceX's wildly busy year continues with astronaut splashdown
SUMMARY: Three NASA astronauts and a European astronaut splashed down aboard their SpaceX Crew Dragon capsule off the coast of Florida after midnight Friday morning, capping off their six-month mission during which they worked alongside Russian cosmonauts and hosted the first all-private crew to visit the orbiting outpost.

TITLE: Harassment is a problem in VR, and it's likely to get worse
SUMMARY: If you believe Mark Zuckerberg, the future is virtual.

TITLE: Amazon Labor Union's Chris Smalls faces off against Sen. Graham on workers
SUMMARY: The president of the Amazon Labor Union warned Sen. Lindsey Graham on Thursday that he risks ignoring the concerns of workers at his own political peril.

TITLE: DoorDash's business continues to boom two years into the pandemic
SUMMARY: DoorDash, which went public amid a pandemic-fueled delivery craze in late 2020, said its business continues to boom even as people increasingly return to their lives outside the home.

TITLE: Meta announces plans to slow hiring following challenging quarter
SUMMARY: Meta said Thursday it is cutting back on hiring. The move is one of several shifts the Facebook parent company is making following a period of slower-than-usual growth.

TITLE: Elon Musk raises an additional $7 billion in financing for Twitter deal
SUMMARY: Elon Musk has raised just over $7 billion in additional equity financing to help fund his purchase of Twitter.

TITLE: Bill Gates doubts Musk's Twitter buy, says draft SCOTUS decision overturning Roe is 'pretty disappointing'
SUMMARY: Bill Gates sounded a note of caution this week on Elon Musk's $44 billion acquisition of Twitter, saying the Tesla CEO "actually could make it worse" despite a strong track record with his other business ventures.

TITLE: Here's what it's like to have a robot paint your nails for $10
SUMMARY: On a recent April afternoon I tossed a few things into a basket at Target — cereal, graham crackers, kids' sunglasses — then sat down at the end of an aisle filled with beauty items, placed a hand into a box-like machine, and let a robot paint my fingernails.

TITLE: SpaceX's jam-packed schedule continues with another astronaut return
SUMMARY: Three NASA astronauts and a European astronaut are returning home from the International Space Station, capping off their six-month mission during which they worked alongside Russian cosmonauts and hosted the first all-private crew to visit the orbiting outpost.

TITLE: New York City pension funds sue Activision Blizzard, seeking records on CEO Bobby Kotick
SUMMARY: New York City pension fund officials sued Activision Blizzard late last month in a bid to force the company to disclose records that may uncover whether CEO Bobby Kotick breached his fiduciary duty to investors, according to a newly released copy of the complaint.

TITLE: Elon Musk says fees for some users may be coming to Twitter
SUMMARY: Elon Musk said Twitter might soon charge fees for certain users, as the billionaire continues to tease how he might change the platform as its new owner.

TITLE: Airbnb to crack down on parties during summer holidays
SUMMARY: Airbnb is once again trying to stop people from using its platform to host unauthorized parties ahead of key summer holidays.

TITLE: VP Harris to meet with Amazon Labor Union and other grassroots organizers
SUMMARY: Vice President Kamala Harris and Labor Secretary Marty Walsh will meet with union leaders Thursday including Christian Smalls, the former Amazon employee who helped successfully organize workers at an Amazon facility in Staten Island.

TITLE: Airbnb's business is booming — and rates are rising
SUMMARY: Airbnb reported more than 100 million bookings during the first quarter of this year, a record for the company that underscores the turnaround from when its business was decimated in the early months of the pandemic. The resurgence in demand has sent the company's rental rates to new heights as well.
